@node "Conflict" "Library Conflicts"

  @{b}@{fg shine}@{bg fill}Library number conflicts@{ub}@{fg text}@{bg back}

  You'll know that you have a library number conflict if
  you find that commands either refuse to tokenise (ie
  change colour to show that Blitz recognises them), or
  you may find that when they do tokenise, they change to a
  totally different command!

  BlitzLibMan will sort it out - read further on the @{i}Usage @{ui}
  page.
@endnode

